<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="564" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1494,2023]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,536]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="564" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,1494,1519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Redescription.</emphasis>
Female (
<typeStatus box="[483,588,1494,1519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">holotype</typeStatus>
). 
<emphasis box="[609,719,1494,1518]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Body size</emphasis>
: 
<quantity box="[737,826,1495,1519]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[844,931,1494,1519]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number box="[900,931,1495,1519]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[954,1077,1494,1518]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Coloration</emphasis>
: integument primarily metallic green; vertex, pronotum and scutum metallic green with large dull areas (
<figureCitation box="[988,1073,1530,1555]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number box="[1041,1073,1531,1555]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); metasoma metallic green with large membranous whitish borders basolaterally; sterna greenish; wing membrane light with brown veins; femora and tibiae greenish; tarsi brownish. 
<emphasis box="[563,624,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Head</emphasis>
: scapal basin with distinct transverse zones of cross-ridging (
<figureCitation box="[1336,1423,1602,1627]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1423,1603,1627]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
); scape and pedicel greenish; flagellomeres dark brown; malar space extremely short (about 
<number box="[1272,1307,1639,1663]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="0.3">0.3</number>
× 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" box="[1354,1424,1639,1663]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">MOD</collectionCode>
); subantennal space narrow, shorter than 
<number box="[626,661,1674,1699]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="0.5">0.5</number>
× 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" box="[704,773,1675,1699]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">MOD</collectionCode>
; genal fringe well developed; genal region, behind the composed eye, with distinct scratch marks (
<figureCitation box="[646,730,1710,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number box="[699,730,1711,1735]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
); upper genal space broad (longer than 
<number box="[1179,1214,1710,1735]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="2.5">2.5</number>
× 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" box="[1246,1316,1711,1735]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14382" name="University of Modena and Reggio Emilia, Department of Biology" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">MOD</collectionCode>
); posterior genal margin delimited by carina; upper frons with regular and deep punctures; vertex without punctuation; genal space with scarce and widely separated punctures. 
<emphasis box="[726,779,1783,1806]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Legs</emphasis>
: fore femur elbowed basally, forming strong ventral keellike projection; tarsal claws with two subsidiary teeth; legs without distinct punctures, except by tiny ones noticed externally. 
<emphasis box="[276,343,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Wings</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[361,393,1855,1879]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
R 
<number box="[381,393,1855,1879]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="1.0">1</number>
</emphasis>
absent; 
<emphasis box="[489,512,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">M</emphasis>
strongly arched, arising slightly before at 
<emphasis box="[998,1053,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">cu–a</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[1069,1097,1855,1878]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Rs</emphasis>
short and curving away from distal margin of wing. 
<emphasis box="[409,520,1891,1914]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Pronotum</emphasis>
: lower lateral pronotal surface with large and deep fovea; dorsal surface without punctuation, scarce punctures noticed antero and laterally (
<figureCitation box="[814,899,1926,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number box="[867,899,1927,1951]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); integument dull, with pulverulent air (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Fig. 19, 20</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[208,355,1962,1986]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Mesopleuron</emphasis>
: omaulus and scrobal carina very sharp; mesopleural surface coarsely punctuated. 
<emphasis box="[1344,1435,1963,1986]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">Scutum:</emphasis>
notauli absent (
<figureCitation box="[334,423,1998,2023]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="563">
Fig. 
<number box="[391,423,1999,2023]" pageId="8" pageNumber="563" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface without punctuation along scutal area, scarce punctation restricted to posterolateral region; disc with integument dull, with pulverulent air (
<figureCitation box="[964,1052,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 19, 20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1432,1455]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,638,1411]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[162,1424,638,1411]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19, 20. Elampus pulchricollis, holotype, ♀. 19. Habitus, lateral view. 20. Pronotum, dorsal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264651/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number box="[1020,1052,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1074,1201,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Metanotum</emphasis>
: pointed posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[159,246,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,246,188,212]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
); coarsely punctuated. 
<emphasis box="[512,651,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Propodeum:</emphasis>
with sharp teeth basolaterally. 
<emphasis box="[1014,1130,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Metasoma</emphasis>
: lateral margins of visible terga with large membranous whitish border (
<figureCitation box="[672,757,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number box="[726,757,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
); T 
<number box="[799,811,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="3.0">3</number>
distal margin with shallow medial notch (
<figureCitation box="[1296,1379,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number box="[1350,1379,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) and smooth integument; T 
<number box="[403,413,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="1.0">1</number>
and T 
<number box="[487,501,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="2.0">2</number>
with tiny and widely separated punctures, very shiny interspaces; fine punctuation at all metasoma (
<figureCitation box="[342,424,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1553,1576]" captionTargetBox="[227,1360,595,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[219,1368,591,1532]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 24. Elampus pulchricollis. 21. T 3 apical margin, posterior view, punctures omitted on right side. 22. Metanotum, dorsal view, punctures omitted. 23. Metasoma, lateral view. 24. Head, frontal view. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264652/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
Fig. 
<number box="[394,424,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
), larger and deeper on T 
<number box="[701,714,296,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564" value="3.0">3</number>
, mainly anterolaterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,536]" box="[199,838,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">Variation.</emphasis>
The species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[732,834,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="564">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
